WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified optical DNA profile for the Nikon NIKKOR Z 50mm f/1.2 S‑Line
lens. It covers the Nano Crystal Coat gradient‑index effect, ARNEO coat,
SR (Short‑wavelength Refractive) glass, Phase Fresnel element (when present
in telephoto variants, here for reference), and the Z‑mount geometry that
reduces vignetting.

WHY IT EXISTS
Nikon’s S‑Line lenses exploit the 55 mm inner diameter and 16 mm flange
focal distance of the Z‑mount to place large rear elements close to the
sensor. This file mathematically captures those design advantages, enabling
correct virtual production and VFX integration for Nikon‑shot content.

HOW IT WORKS
- Nano Crystal Coat: gradient‑index layer, δn ≈ 0 at boundary; reflectance
  < 0.1% over 380–780 nm.
- ARNEO coat: targets near‑vertical incident light, complements Nano Crystal.
- SR glass: n_blue unusually high, corrects secondary spectrum → negligible
  purple fringing.
- PF element (diffractive): f ∝ λ/Λ, bends light opposite to refraction;
  reduces telephoto length.
- Z‑mount geometry: inner Ø 55 mm, flange distance 16 mm; enables rear
  element placement that minimizes corner shading (< 0.5 EV at f/1.2).
- Distortion: k1 = -0.005, k2 = 0.001 (nearly zero).

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
Nikon Z9/V‑RAPTOR N‑RAW workflows, virtual production, lens simulation.

WHO USES IT
L2 Engineers working with Nikon RAW; L3 Colorists checking corner colour
shift.

WHAT PROBLEM IT SOLVES
Provides the measured advantage of the Z‑mount over F‑mount for wide‑angle
and fast lenses. Eliminates guesswork in vignetting and CA correction for
S‑Line glass.

